---
import SectionHeading from "@/components/SectionHeading.astro";
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "@/site.config";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Haley Parks, an AI Product Engineer building personal AI systems, human modeling tools, and adaptive performance systems."
>
  <section class="interior-container about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Hi, I'm Haley.</h1>
      <p class="about-deck">
        AI Product Engineer, systems thinker, and bodybuilder building software
        that understands people.
      </p>
      <ul class="metadata-row" aria-label="About Haley Parks">
        <li>AI Product Engineer</li>
        <li>{siteConfig.location}</li>
        <li>Human-centered systems</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <aside
      class="contact-card pinned-note workspace-object surface-lavender tape-center"
      aria-labelledby="contact"
    >
      <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
      <h2 id="contact">Open to relevant work</h2>
      <p>{siteConfig.availability}</p>
      <div class="contact-links">
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>Email</a>
        <a href={siteConfig.githubUrl}>GitHub</a>
        <a href={siteConfig.linkedinUrl}>LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section about-build-section">
    <div class="interior-container about-build">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="How I build"
        title="Systems first, people always"
      />
      <div class="about-text-flow">
        <p>
          My work usually starts with a messy human problem, then turns into
          software, data models, dashboards, automation, or conversational
          interfaces that can be used, evaluated, and improved.
        </p>
        <p>
          I am drawn to systems where the interesting part is not one isolated
          metric, page, or workflow, but the relationships between them. Context
          matters. History matters. Goals change. Good tools should help people
          notice those patterns instead of asking them to hold everything in
          their heads.
        </p>
        <blockquote>
          Give the machines the burden of remembering, coordinating, searching,
          and connecting. Give people their attention back.
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section interior-container">
    <article class="bodybuilding-note workspace-object surface-raspberry">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Bodybuilding</p>
        <h2>The Human Model started under a barbell</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="stack">
        <p>
          Outside of work, I am also a bodybuilder. Like many athletes, I wanted
          a deeper understanding of my training than current wearables and
          fitness apps could provide.
        </p>
        <p>
          Recovery metrics are useful, and I rely heavily on data from my Apple
          Watch, but they only tell part of the story. They do not tell me how
          well I am moving, how much force I am producing, how much effort a set
          actually required, or whether I am creating the training stimulus I
          intended.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Human Model began as an attempt to answer those questions for
          myself. Along the way, it became a research platform where I can
          experiment with wearable data, biomechanics, machine learning,
          conversational interfaces, and decision-support systems to better
          understand how people adapt over time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section focus-section">
    <div class="interior-container about-grid">
      <SectionHeading eyebrow="Current focus" title="What I am looking for" />
      <div class="focus-grid">
        <article class="focus-object focus-raspberry workspace-object no-tape">
          <h3>AI product engineering</h3>
          <p>
            Turning ambiguous product ideas into useful systems with clear
            feedback loops, thoughtful interfaces, and honest boundaries.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="focus-object focus-lavender workspace-object no-tape">
          <h3>Personal AI systems</h3>
          <p>
            Building software that understands people through context, history,
            goals, and evidence rather than one-off prompts.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="focus-object focus-plant workspace-object no-tape">
          <h3>Adaptive performance systems</h3>
          <p>
            Exploring how data, modeling, and human judgment can support better
            decisions as a person changes over time.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="focus-object focus-olive workspace-object no-tape">
          <h3>Human-centered automation</h3>
          <p>
            Giving machines the remembering and coordination work while keeping
            people in control of judgment, taste, and direction.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section interior-container">
    <aside class="opportunity-note workspace-object surface-ochre tape-left">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Opportunities</p>
        <h2>Useful systems, honest boundaries, real users.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        I am easiest to reach by email, and my public repositories are linked
        from the contact note above.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(18rem, 0.34fr);
    gap: var(--section-gap);
    align-items: end;
    padding-block: clamp(2.75rem, 5.5vw, 5rem);
  }

  .about-hero-copy {
    max-width: 790px;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    max-width: 11ch;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--font-size-page-title);
    line-height: 0.98;
  }

  .about-deck {
    max-width: 740px;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--font-size-supporting);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.18;
  }

  .pinned-note,
  .opportunity-note {
    position: relative;
  }

  .pinned-note {
    --object-tilt: 0.45deg;
    border-left: 0.38rem solid var(--houseplant);
    padding: var(--space-5);
  }

  .contact-card h2,
  .opportunity-note h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2vw, 1.8rem);
  }

  .contact-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-strong);
  }

  .about-build-section,
  .focus-section {
    border-block: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
    background: var(--color-surface-band);
  }

  .about-build {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.64fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: var(--section-gap);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-text-flow {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-text-flow p,
  .bodybuilding-note p,
  .opportunity-note p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  blockquote {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 0;
    border-left: 0.35rem solid var(--rust);
    padding: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.7rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.22;
  }

  .bodybuilding-note {
    --object-tilt: -0.25deg;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.56fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: var(--section-gap);
    border-left: 0.38rem solid var(--rust);
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
  }

  .bodybuilding-note h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--font-size-section-title);
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.8fr) minmax(0, 1.2fr);
    gap: var(--section-gap);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-grid p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .focus-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .focus-object {
    --focus-accent: var(--rust);
    --focus-surface: var(--color-surface-raised);
    min-width: 0;
    border-top: 0.36rem solid var(--focus-accent);
    padding: var(--space-5);
    background: var(--focus-surface);
  }

  .focus-object:nth-child(2),
  .focus-object:nth-child(3) {
    --object-tilt: -0.35deg;
  }

  .focus-object h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
  }

  .focus-raspberry {
    --focus-accent: var(--rust);
    --focus-surface: color-mix(in srgb, var(--rust) 8%, var(--paper));
  }

  .focus-lavender {
    --focus-accent: var(--lavender);
    --focus-surface: color-mix(in srgb, var(--lavender) 34%, var(--paper));
  }

  .focus-plant {
    --focus-accent: var(--houseplant);
    --focus-surface: color-mix(in srgb, var(--houseplant) 12%, var(--paper));
  }

  .focus-olive {
    --focus-accent: var(--olive);
    --focus-surface: color-mix(in srgb, var(--olive) 14%, var(--paper));
  }

  .opportunity-note {
    --object-tilt: 0.25deg;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.52fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-8);
    width: min(980px, 100%);
    border-left: 0.38rem solid var(--khaki);
    padding: var(--space-5);
  }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .about-hero,
    .about-build,
    .bodybuilding-note,
    .about-grid,
    .focus-grid,
    .opportunity-note {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-hero h1 {
      max-width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
